               <head>Bahr al-mavvaj</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Baḥr al-mavvāj by Muḥammad ʿAlī Khān Anṣārī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85148201 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3994-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_3163208034207230192">Muḥammad ʿAlī Khān Anṣārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_3163208034207230192" type="supplied">محمّد على خان انصارى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8613">Baḥr al-mavvāj</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8613">بحر الموّاج</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Universal history, with special reference to India</p>
                        <p>Extract consists of accounts for Timurid or Mughal rulers, extending from the reign of Emperor <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_48143049" role="subject">Farrukh Siyar</persName> to Emperor <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_45680638" role="subject">Muḥammad Shāh</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The work has been considered to be identical with the <title>Tārīkh-i Muẓaffarī </title>of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_3163208034207230192" role="aut">Muḥammad ʿAlī Khān Anṣārī</persName>. However, according to Storey, the present work is distinguished by its tripartite division into volumes
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
